getImage(uint256[]).details: It runs the connected `StorageContract` in the registered order, gets XML tags of SVG image and combines it into one image. It should be noted that the order in which the asset storage contract is registered must be carefully observed.

params.attrs_: Array of corresponding property values sequentially for each connected contract.

returns._0: A complete SVG image in the form of a String.

getStorageCount().details: Instead of storing the count of storage separately in `PropertyContract`, get the value through this function and use it.

getStorageCount().notice: Returns the count of connected Asset Storages.

_setAttr(uint256).details: Set the attribute value of the corresponding `imageId_` sequentially according to the number of asset storage.

params.imageId_: The token ID for which you want to set the attribute value.

setAssembleContract(address).details: If later changes or extensions are unnecessary, write directly to `constructor` without implementing the function.

params.newAssembleContractAddr_: Address value of `AssembleContract` to be changed.
